# Repositories Style

- Repositories are thin interfaces extending `JpaRepository<Entity, Long>`.
- Keep `@Repository` on interfaces for clarity and consistent style.
- Add only targeted finder methods needed by services (for example `findByEmail`, `findByFileName`).
- Use `Optional<T>` for finder return values unless null semantics are intentionally required in service code.
- Avoid business logic in repository layer; put orchestration in services.
